<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="30" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="30">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="30">
This species was redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Matsumura, Y" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="17" pageNumber="34" pagination="1533 - 1561" publicationUrl="10.1080/00222933.2011.559594" refId="B13" refString="Matsumura, Y, Sasaki, S, Imasaka, S, Sano, M, and, Ohara M, 2011. Revision of the Lema (Lema) concinnipennis Baly, 1865 species group (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Criocerinae) in Japan. Journal of Natural History 45: 1533 - 1561, 10.1080/00222933.2011.559594" title="Revision of the Lema (Lema) concinnipennis Baly, 1865 species group (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Criocerinae) in Japan." url="10.1080/00222933.2011.559594" volume="45" year="2011">Matsumura et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
who presumed 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Campanulales" pageId="13" pageNumber="30" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="japonicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="30">Cirsium japonicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
DC and 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Lema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suffultum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="30">Lema suffultum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Matsum. (
<taxonomicName genus="Asteraceae" lsidName="" pageId="13" pageNumber="30" rank="genus">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
) to be its host plants. Here 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Asteraceae" genus="Cirsium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Campanulales" pageId="13" pageNumber="30" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="japonicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="30">Cirsium japonicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 43â€“48" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figures 43 - 48. Live adults or larvae in the field. 43 - 44 Lema diversipes on Pueraria lobata (Willd.) subsp. thomsonii (Benth.) Ohashi 43 a pair of adults 44 a cluster of larvae 45 - 46 Lema lacertosa on Commelina communis L. 45 adult 46 larva 47 - 48 Lema cyanella on Cirsium japonicum 47 adult 48 larva." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/27237" pageId="13" pageNumber="30">Figs 47-48</figureCitation>
) is confirmed as a host plant by field observations and laboratory rearing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
